The paper discusses measurement practices in Agile Software Development (ASD) methods, which are primarily concerned with software engineering (cs.SE) and software measurement (cs.MS). The paper also mentions the differences between Agile and traditional software development methods, which falls under programming languages (cs.PL) and software design (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper briefly discusses the Agile version of Common Software Measurement International Consortium (COSMIC) publication, which relates to cybersecurity (cs.CY).
